title: (Crystallographic) space group types (230 in three dimensions). Two space groups, considered as subgroups of the group of affine transformations of space, have the same space group type if they are conjugate by an orientation-preserving affine transformation. In three dimensions, for 11 of the affine space groups, there is no orientation-preserving map from the group to its mirror image, so if one distinguishes groups from their mirror images these each split into two cases. So there are 54+11=65 space group types that preserve orientation.

(Crystallographic) space group types (230 in three dimensions). Two space groups, considered as subgroups of the group of affine transformations of space, have the same space group type if they are conjugate by an orientation-preserving affine transformation. In three dimensions, for 11 of the affine space groups, there is no orientation-preserving map from the group to its mirror image, so if one distinguishes groups from their mirror images these each split into two cases. So there are 54+11=65 space group types that preserve orientation.

table-1382-551.caption: NBC Studio productions
data: Debuted October 22, 2007, and is the home to MSNBC programs. An MSNBC/NBC News Newsroom connects control room 2K and studio floor 3A.

The first studio in the building to be converted for Television production, being converted in 1935 and served as NBC Television's lone studio until the conversion of Studio 8G in 1948. 3H was adjacent to Studio 3C. This studio has been decommissioned since the early 1960s and served as scenery storage for a number of decades. Small portions of Studio 3C have been expanded into this area..

The current home of such web based shows as "The Untitled News Comedy Show", "Starstruck", and "A Big Life with Sissy Biggers". Was previously home to a small set for WNBC as well as WNBC's Master control.
Former home of Early Today and MSNBC secondly studio (Ed Show home and Breaking News coverage), called as "Newsnooks". This space was previously a portion of WNBC's Master Control.

A "Studio 8A" is marked on an official drawing of the 8th floor of the building. Judging by the surrounding area, this studio was likely used for audio recording. It's possible this studio was converted to television studio 8B.

data: Croatia submits answers to the Commission's Questionnaire.
European Commission replies to the answers with a positive opinion (Avis).
European Council sets the date for the entry negotiations to begin 2005-03-17.
Beginning of negotiations (shortly after midnight in Luxembourg).
1 chapter is opened & closed: Science & Research.
2 chapters are opened: Competition Policy and Customs Union.
1 chapter is opened: Social Policy & Employment.
1 chapter is opened & closed: Education & Culture.
1 chapter is opened: Intellectual Property Law.
6 chapters are opened: Company Law, Financial Control, Financial Services, Information Society & Media, Right of Establishment & Freedom To Provide Services, and Statistics.
2 chapters are opened: Consumer & Health Protection and External Relations.
2 chapters are opened: Trans-European Networks and Financial & Budgetary Provisions.
2 chapters are opened: Energy and Transport Policy.
2 chapters are opened: Freedom of Movement For Workers and Social Policy & Employment.
1 chapter is opened: Free Movement of Goods. 1 chapter is closed: Enterprise & Industrial Policy.
1 chapter is opened: Public Procurement. 3 chapters are closed: Economic & Monetary Policy, Information Society & Media, and Intellectual Property Law.
Croatia closed 5 chapters & opened 6. Chapters that were closed: Company Law, Customs Union, Freedom of Movement of Workers, Statistics, and Trans-European Networks.
3 chapters are closed: Consumer & Health Protection, Energy, and Financial Services.
2 chapters are closed: Right of Establishment & Freedom To Provide Services and Social Policy & Employment.
1 chapter is closed: Free Movement of Goods.
2 chapters are closed: Taxation and Public Procurement. 3 chapters are opened: Foreign, Security & Defence Policy, Judiciary & Fundamental Rights, and Competition Policy.
2 chapters are closed: Food Safety, Veterinary & Phytosanitary Policy and Financial Control.
3 chapters are closed: Institutions, Transport Policy and Free Movement of Capital.
3 chapters are closed: 24. Justice, Freedom & Security, 27. Environment and 31. Foreign, Security & Defence Policy.
2 chapters are closed: 11. Agriculture & Rural Development, 22. Regional Policy & Coordination of Structural Instruments
Commission recommends closing of the negotiations and sets 2013-07-01 as target entry date
European Council calls for finishing negotiations by the end of June and signing of the Treaty of Accession by the end of 2011
End of accession negotiations. Final 4 chapters are closed: 8. Competition Policy, 23. Judiciary & Fundamental Rights, 33. Financial & Budgetary Provisions and 35. Other Issues.
Commission adopts a favourable opinion on Croatia's accession to the EU
European Parliament approves Croatia's entry to the EU.
